The paper deals with the study of graphs and their properties, which is a common theme in computer science. The concept of double-threshold graphs is related to pairwise compatibility graphs and bipartite permutation graphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithmic aspect of recognizing double-threshold graphs suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of graph theory and its applications to optimization problems is also a topic in theoretical computer science, which could place the paper in the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
